ated with the use of ibuprofen in two liver transplant recipients on FK506." Transplantation 57 (1994):  1132-3[2] "Product Information. Prograf (tacrolimus)." Fujisawa  (2001):[3] "Product Information. Rapamune (sirolimus)." Wyeth-Ayerst Laboratories  (2001):', 'Alteplase, Ascorbic acid, Vitamin A, Potassium Iodide, Cyclosporine, Acetylcysteine, Nandrolone, Heparin, Golimumab, Cyclosporine, Ustekinumab, More', NULL, 1767369485);
