A 269 (1993):  2110-2[6] Thorn GW "Clinical considerations in the use of corticosteroids." N Engl J Med 274 (1966):  775-81[7] "Product Information. Hydeltrasol (prednisolone)." Merck & Co., Inc  (2001):[8] Ramsahoye BH, Davies SV, el-Gaylani N, Sandeman D, Scanlon MF "The mineralocorticoid effects of high dose hydrocortisone." BMJ 310 (1995):  656-7', 'Tinidazole, Ascorbic acid, Simeprevir, Sulfadiazine, Lactic acid, Probenecid, Tioconazole, Brinzolamide, Furazolidone, Diiodohydroxyquinoline, Oxytetracycline, More', 'Formoterol, Cromoglicic acid, Ipratropium, Isoprenaline, Tiotropium, Terbutaline, Aclidinium, Glycopyrronium, Mometasone, Fluticasone, Salbutamol, More', 1767369485);
